<% content_for :title, "What an AI feature is actually made of — tokenprice.fyi" %>
<% content_for :description, "A feature is a chain of calls, each with a different job. The step that drives the bill and the step that needs the capable model are usually different ones. Worked call-chains for a chatbot, RAG, an agent loop, and classification." %>
<% content_for :canonical, learn_anatomy_url %>
<% content_for :og_type, "article" %>
<% content_for :head do %>
  <%= json_ld({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
        headline: "What an AI feature is actually made of",
        datePublished: "2026-06-01",
        author: { "@type": "Organization", name: "tokenprice.fyi", url: root_url },
        publisher: { "@type": "Organization", name: "tokenprice.fyi", url: root_url },
        mainEntityOfPage: learn_anatomy_url }) %>
  <%= json_ld({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
        itemListElement: [
          { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Learn", item: learn_url },
          { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: "What an AI feature is actually made of", item: learn_anatomy_url }
        ] }) %>
<% end %>
<%= render "shared/explainer_styles" %>

<style>
  /* Call-chain diagram — the worked feature pattern, rendered from FeaturePattern. */
  .ac-chain { margin: 22px 0 16px; }
  .ac-chain-head { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .ac-chain-name { font-size: 17px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--color-slate-900); }
  .ac-chain-blurb { font-size: 14px; color: var(--color-slate-500); }
  .ac-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }
  .ac-step { display: grid; grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto; align-items: center; gap: 14px;
    padding: 12px 14px; border: 1px solid var(--color-slate-200); border-radius: var(--radius-md); background: #fff; }
  .ac-step-no { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-slate-400); }
  .ac-step-id { min-width: 0; }
  .ac-step-role { font-size: 14.5px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-slate-900); }
  .ac-step-purpose { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--color-slate-500); }
  .ac-step-tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; justify-content: flex-end; }
  .ac-flag { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600;
    padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 999px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .ac-flag-cost { background: #fffbeb; color: #b45309; }
  .ac-flag-cap { background: #eef2ff; color: #4338ca; }
  .ac-flag-loop { background: #f1f5f9; color: var(--color-slate-500); }
  .ac-arrow { text-align: center; color: var(--color-slate-300); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1; padding: 2px 0; }
  .ac-read { font-size: 14.5px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-slate-700); margin: 14px 0 4px;
    padding: 12px 16px; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-slate-200); background: var(--color-slate-50); border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0; }
  .ac-read strong { color: var(--color-slate-900); }
  .ac-callout { margin: 40px 0 8px; padding: 24px 26px; border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: var(--color-slate-900); color: #fff; }
  .ac-callout p { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; font-weight: 600; color: #fff; margin: 0; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .ac-step { grid-template-columns: auto 1fr; }
    .ac-step-tags { grid-column: 1 / -1; justify-content: flex-start; }
  }
</style>

<article class="hp">
  <p class="hp-meta"><%= link_to "Learn", learn_path %> › Feature anatomy · June 2026</p>
  <h1>What an AI feature is actually made of.</h1>
  <p class="hp-subtitle">A feature is a chain of calls, each with a different job. The step that drives the bill and the step that needs the capable model are usually different ones.</p>

  <p>The thing people picture as one model call is almost never one call. A support chatbot classifies the message, retrieves help-centre passages, then writes a reply. A coding agent plans, edits, runs tools, and re-checks across many steps. Each link in the chain has a different job, a different token shape, and a different right model.</p>

  <p>Two of those steps matter most, and they pull in opposite directions. One step is the <strong>cost-driver step</strong>: where the tokens, and so the bill, concentrate. Another is the <strong>capable-model step</strong>: the one that actually needs a frontier model to get the job right. The common mistake is putting one frontier model across the whole chain because a single step needs it.</p>

  <p>The fix is to read the chain step by step. Below are four common shapes, each rendered from the same data the guide uses. For each, the cost-driver step and the capable-model step are named from the chain itself.</p>

  <% if @frontier_example&.input && @frontier_example&.output %>
    <p>The capable-model step is where a frontier price is worth paying. Today the cheapest frontier model on the index is <strong><%= @frontier_example.name %></strong>, at <span class="num"><%= usd_plain(@frontier_example.input) %></span> in / <span class="num"><%= usd_plain(@frontier_example.output) %></span> out per 1M tokens. Put that rate on one step that needs it, not on every step that doesn't.</p>
  <% end %>

  <% @patterns.each do |pattern| %>
    <hr>
    <div class="ac-chain">
      <div class="ac-chain-head">
        <span class="ac-chain-name"><%= pattern.label %></span>
        <span class="ac-chain-blurb"><%= pattern.blurb %></span>
      </div>
      <div class="ac-steps">
        <% pattern.steps.each_with_index do |step, i| %>
          <% if i.positive? %><div class="ac-arrow">↓</div><% end %>
          <div class="ac-step">
            <span class="ac-step-no num"><%= format("%02d", i + 1) %></span>
            <div class="ac-step-id">
              <div class="ac-step-role"><%= step.role %></div>
              <div class="ac-step-purpose"><%= step.purpose %></div>
            </div>
            <div class="ac-step-tags">
              <%= tier_badge(step.tier) %>
              <% if step.loops? %><span class="ac-flag ac-flag-loop">loops</span><% end %>
              <% if step.cost_driver? %><span class="ac-flag ac-flag-cost">cost-driver step</span><% end %>
              <% if step.capability? %><span class="ac-flag ac-flag-cap">capable-model step</span><% end %>
            </div>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
      <% anatomy_chain_reading(pattern).each do |line| %>
        <p class="ac-read"><%= raw line %></p>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  <% end %>

  <div class="ac-callout">
    <p>The cost-driver step and the capable-model step are usually different.</p>
  </div>

  <hr>
  <h2>Where this goes next</h2>
  <p>The shapes above are the skeleton. Two pages put numbers and choices on them.</p>

  <div class="hp-cta">
    <%= link_to learn_feature_costs_path, class: "hp-cta-ghost" do %>
      The worked cost breakdown behind these shapes
    <% end %>
    <%= link_to guide_path, class: "hp-cta-ghost" do %>
      See starting options in the guide
    <% end %>
  </div>
</article>
